properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 5:39PM AKST until January 9 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches tonight.

* WHERE...Prince of Wales Island and the southern Inner Channels
including Ketchikan.

* WHEN...Tonight.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Another more potent winter storm will
potentially bring 6 to 12 inches of snow Thursday night into
Friday morning. This storm could persist into Friday evening.
properties.instruction:
An advisory means that a potentially hazardous event is already
occurring or imminent.

A watch means conditions are favorable of the development winter
storm conditions in and close to the watch area.

Preparation for this potentially dangerous weather event should
begin now.
